#ex2 ##Exploring the count tables

#1
library(compGenomRData)
counts_file <- system.file("extdata/rna-seq/SRP029880.raw_counts.tsv",package = "compGenomRData")
coldata_file <- system.file("extdata/rna-seq/SRP029880.colData.tsv",package = "compGenomRData")

counts <- as.matrix(read.table(counts_file, header = T, sep = '\t'))
metadata <-  as.matrix(read.table(coldata_file,sep="\t", stringsAsFactors = FALSE,row.names = 1))

#1
geneLengths_mat <- subset(counts, select = c(width))
geneLengths_vector <- as.vector(geneLengths_mat)

rpkm <- apply(X = subset(counts, select = c(-width)),
              MARGIN = 2,
              FUN = function(x) {
              (x * 10^9) / (geneLengths_vector * sum(as.numeric(x)))
              })

colSums(rpkm)
##   CASE_1   CASE_2   CASE_3   CASE_4   CASE_5   CTRL_1   CTRL_2   CTRL_3 
## 158291.0 153324.2 161775.4 173047.4 172761.4 210032.6 301764.2 241418.3 
##   CTRL_4   CTRL_5 
## 291674.5 252005.7
tpm <- apply(rpkm, 2, function(x) {(x / sum(as.numeric(x))) * 10^6})

colSums(tpm)
## CASE_1 CASE_2 CASE_3 CASE_4 CASE_5 CTRL_1 CTRL_2 CTRL_3 CTRL_4 CTRL_5 
##  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06  1e+06
#2
library(pheatmap)
##settin up the data
mostvar <- as.matrix(names(sort(apply(tpm, 1, var),decreasing=TRUE)[1:500]))
dim(mostvar)
## [1] 500   1
mostvar2 <- as.matrix(names(sort(apply(tpm, 1, var),decreasing=TRUE)[1:100]))
dim(mostvar2)
## [1] 100   1
##heat maps
pheatmap(tpm[mostvar,], 
         scale = "row", 
         clustering_method = "complete",
         border_color=NA,
         color = colorRampPalette(rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))(256),
         show_rownames=FALSE)

pheatmap(tpm[mostvar2,], 
         scale = "row", 
         clustering_method = "complete",
         border_color=NA,
         color = colorRampPalette(rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))(256),
         show_rownames=FALSE)

#4
library(stats)
library(corrplot)
## Warning: package 'corrplot' was built under R version 4.1.1
## corrplot 0.90 loaded
##correlat plot
correlationMatrix <- cor(tpm)
corrplot(correlationMatrix, order = "hclust",type="upper",
addrect = 2, addCoef.col = "black",method="ellipse",
number.cex = 0.7,hclust.method = "average")

#5
#extracting the 100 genes that have the highest total expression in all samples
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
totalexpression <- as.matrix(rowSums(tpm))
highestexpress <- as.matrix(totalexpression[totalexpression %in% tail(sort(totalexpression),100),])
dim(highestexpress)
## [1] 100   1
highsttpm <- as.matrix(tpm[rownames(tpm) %in% rownames(highestexpress),])
#heat map
pheatmap(highsttpm, 
         clustering_method = "complete",
         scale = "row",
         border_color=NA,
         color = colorRampPalette(rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))(256),
         show_rownames=FALSE)

#6
#heat map with annotations
annotation <- data.frame(sampletype=metadata[,1], 
                         row.names=rownames(metadata))
pheatmap(tpm[mostvar,], 
         clustering_method = "complete",
         annotation = annotation,
         scale = "row",
         color = colorRampPalette(rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))(256),
         show_rownames=FALSE)

#PCA with annotations
